en.intro: The extruder nozzle temperature is abnormal and cannot reach the set value. This may be caused by an improperly installed nozzle silicone sock.
Nozzle clumping detection calibration failed. Excessive force detected on the nozzle. Please ensure the nozzle is installed correctly.
Nozzle clumping detection calibration failed. The nozzle did not touch the inner wall of the hole. Please clean the nozzle and the steel plate hole at the rear-right side of the heatbed.
The extruder is extruding abnormally. It may be clogged, or the filament may be too thin, causing the extruder to slip, or the externally mounted filament may be tangled.
The extrusion resistance is abnormal. The extruder may be clogged or there may be filament stuck in the toolhead, or the externally mounted filament may be tangled.
The Left Side Auxiliary Component Cooling Fan speed is slow. It may be stuck and need cleaning.
The Left Side Auxiliary Component Cooling Fan speed is slow. It may be stuck and need cleaning.
Time-lapse kit authentication failed. Please reconnect the cable or restart the printer.
Foreign object detection failed, possibly due to manual interruption (e.g., clicking "Stop"). If not, try restarting the printer or updating the firmware.
Threaded rods need lubrication now.
An anomalous jump in the extruder extrusion force sensor data has been detected, potentially caused by poor sensor contact or a faulty sensor.
The chamber heater failed to reach the target temperature.
Foreign object detection is not working. Detected the Live View Camera has been replaced. Please tap "Settings>Calibration" on printer screen and re-calibrate the Live View Camera.
Foreign object detection accuracy has decreased. If this occurs frequently, perform a Live View Camera calibration (“Settings” > “Calibration” on the printer screen).
Foreign object detection is not working. The Live View Camera needs calibration. Please tap "Settings > Calibration" on the printer screen.
Linear rods need cleaning and lubrication now.
Performing initial High-temperature Bed Leveling.
Performing initial High-temperature Bed Leveling.

Heated bed leveling failed, possibly due to foreign objects on the bed or bed tilt. Continuing to print may damage the build plate. Please remove any debris or manually level the bed before retrying.
User information has expired, please log in again.
Vision encoder patterns can not be recognized; possible reasons include vision encoder pattern distortion, light overexposure, and plate misplacement.
